    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-12T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.00/458: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-12T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 12, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>171. Paul Alling, Assistant Chief, Division of Near Eastern Affairs, returning
                    from Geneva, has been directed to stop off at London to consult with Embassy and
                    appropriate British officials concerning developments with respect to
                    Palestine.</p>
                <p>Please afford him every assistance to obtain fullest information that British
                    officials may be willing to disclose informally and confidentially. It is
                    anticipated that the Department will be subjected to severe pressure in
                    connection with the report of the Royal Commission of Inquiry.</p>
                <p>Alling has been instructed to notify Embassy of date of arrival. Please do utmost
                    to procure moderately priced hotel accommodations for him and his wife.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
